
Mongo DB Installation
1.	Go to google and type MongoDB installation community version.
2.	https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
3.	In the nav bar collapse the product module and choose the community edition
4.	Select the download button
5.	Chose the version, platform and the package as msi
6.	Download the package
7.	Open and double click on it and it will get downloaded
8.	Click next on the pop up 
9.	Select complete button and click on agreement and click on next unbutton the mongodb compass.
10.	Once the download part completed open the command prompt and type 
mongod –version.
11.	If you couldn’t find the software.
Open cdrive -- program files-mongodb-server8.2bincopy the pathopen the environment variablesin advance-environment variablessystem variablesselect the pathclick on newpaste the linkclick on ok->okok
12.	Open the command prompt type the command mongod –version.
Mongodb shell installation
1.	Open google and type mongo shell installation
2.	https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/shell
3.	Choose the version, platform and select the package as msi
4.	It will get downloaded
5.	Double click on the software it will show a setup pop up
6.	Uncheck the button
7.	C:/programfiles/mongosh
8.	Nextinstall->finish
9.	Open the cmd and type mongosh
10.	You will find the version of mondodb and mongo shell
11.	Type show dbs
 
